This code is compatilbe with Microsoft Playready PK3 and is tested
on Linux amd64/x86/ARM architectures.

BUILD and SETUP
-------------------


1. Make sure that you build the latest PK3 including the CDMI.

2. Build the code:

  # make -B CDMI_MAKE_CONFIG=config_playready.mk PLAYREADY_DIR=$HOME/playready

where PLAYREADY_DIR is the path to the PK3 build.

3. Copy the test PK3 Samples folder to your the ocdm project:

  # cp ~/playready/Samples test/
  # cd test
  # ../cdmiservice


